173>(6/11/01 6:06:44 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Exploits, Dragons, and Us?</span><hr size=1> I dont know how many people surf the web, check out the new non-whineplay EQ board, or generally keep an eye out on whats happening elsewhere in Everquest beyond Karana, so I thought I'd post this here since it's sort of relevent to our Dragon Raids.<br>
<br>
For those who dont know, recently the guild Conquest from another server was completely disbanded, 2 players banned, and about 26 others suspended for exploitation in the Sleeper's Tomb.  Now the alert I'm brining to everyon's attention is that our (almost everyone who does the dragons) current stratagies have been formally acknowlaged by Verant as warnable and bannable exploits.<br>
<br>
The following is an except, the full text can be found on the Gameplay forum of the official Everquest web site or at the following address: boards.station.sony.com/ubb/everquest/Forum1/HTML/000210.html.<br>
<br>
[&gt; There really is no in-between on sleepers tomb warders - <br>
&gt; clerics just cant <br>
&gt; take the hits. Yet running Back down the steps at nagafen, <br>
&gt; or back into the <br>
&gt; safe hall on nag or vox remains a perfectly valid tactic and <br>
&gt; isn't challenged <br>
&gt; by VI...<br>
<br>
Again, I believe it IS challenged by us. I just called Michelle Butler and talked to her about this. When they do catch people exploiting Nagafen or Vox in this manner they are warned and often removed from the zone and told they can't do the dragon this spawn. If they are on record as repeat offenders in this area, they are suspended. She also said I was welcome to review warning and suspension logs for this on Monday, so I'll probably take a look at them then. ]<br>
<br>
Now then, I dont care if Conquest was right or wrong.  This isnt the place for that discussion.  However, I am concerned about how we take on Naggy and Vox.  From what I read Verant considers anytime a mob can be attacked without it being able to attack back FULLY it is an exploit.  IE: Vox, its common to keep the healers back in the hallway and run back for heals.  However, I dont believe she can attack the healers here since she doesnt fit through the doors and AE attacks are line of sight.  I could be somewhat wrong in this, but the general point will remain, Vox cannot fully attack the healers and just because she can summon them (I dont believe she or Naggy do summon, never have been summoned myself, but since they're above 51 I allow the possibility) doesnt mean its not an exploit.  This means we will have to rethink stratagy or risk being warned and or banned or suspended.<br>
<br>
I do urge everyone to read that and its sister thread mainly to get a glimpse as to Verant's train of thought here.  Since right or wrong, they do set the rules and we need to adjust accordingly if we want to keep playing.<br>
<br>
This also brings up another point.  I've had reservations in the past about having support teams above the 53 limit on the dragon raids.  I think its clear that since the object of the level caps on the dragons is to keep these players from participating in the dragon raids, the use of them for any thing would be considered an exploit.  While using them to help clear/buff does seem to be a gray area, I for one would choose not to chance it.  And as for potentially using them to heal during battles and gate back, that is without a doubt an exploit.  <br>
<br>
From where I stand it looks like Verant is putting the player base on notice that action can and will be taken without warning on things they consider to be bannable.  And whether or not you knew what you did was an exploit does not seem to weigh very much.  At best it will get you 1 warning or a suspension rather than an outright ban.  I urge all guilds to seriously take a look at their tactics both in small groups and any raids you may run and see if there's anything that can be remotely considered an exploit and not do it.  While the complete disbanding of a guild seems like an extreme punishment for what appears to be an exteme event, I dont think you can rule it out as a regular punishment in the future.<br>
<br>
Just my thoughts on a the continuing saga of As Norrath Turns.<br>
<br>
Kellory Silverstar<br>
Druid, 52, Edible<br>
