You don't sit a doctor in the front part of the trenches, and healers have been for centuries considered non-combatants. Hiding the healers from the big mob means that they don't always get attacked the minute they heal someone. <br>
<br>
Vox can and will climb through the wall and get stuck in the wall in an attempt to kill the healers. On the last dragon raid SB did, just this past weekend, Vox reached through a wall and I personally saw the &quot;Azuriem (a cleric in the triage line) has been slain.&quot; message. I have seen Vox run as far as halfway to the gate room down the buff hall, despite the fact that Vox is NOT big enough to even fit through the itty bitty door to her lair (explain that one as not cheating). Vox can and will gate back to her lair when she's at a certain percentage of health, and if there isn't someone there bashing her, she'll complete heal. Nagafen will also reach through walls to kill healers, that's why you make sure not to fight him on the bridge. How about Vox getting stuck in the walls where you can't hit her, but her AE weapon AND her melee attacks can clock people left and right? This was the main reason the Vox rotation moved so fast on Karana, she kept getting stuck in walls. Ever since they upped the aggo on healing, Vox has repeatedly moved into the walls to get at the healers and succeeded. <br>
<br>
This is complete crap. It's no more an exploit than using Rune V and controlling aggro on Venril Sathir. Verant has stacked the deck against us in most of the high level encounters, and telling us they'll ban us for perfectly reasonable tactics is utter hogwash. <br>
