Haemish <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uflarrenlagdalen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Flarren Lagdalen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>King and Queen of Lag</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(6/12/01 11:23:18 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Exploits, Dragons, and Us?</span><hr size=1> Greetings Verant!<br>
<br>
After watching the posts about the Sleepers incident and reading a quote from one of the emails here I am  a) concerned since I am the leader of the dragon raids for the CoG (Council of Guilds) on Karana Server and  b) curious as to some other places I’d like clarification on.<br>
<br>
Obviously being the leader of our Vox and Nagafen raids I am greatly concerned as to what is considered a safe point and what is exploitation. Outside Vox’s lair is not a safe point. On April 8th of this year under Haemish’s leadership with Sacred Band Alliance Vox was taken out. She had become stuck at the door and as soon as she went into run mode she went through the rock door, down the ramp and almost around to the gate room before gating back to her lair. Please check your logs for confirmation of this. I believe it proves that the halls are FAR from safe. Hence having a triage line out there is completely feasible. <br>
<br>
For Nagafen you stated you are concerned that he cannot do the full damage of his potential (example :cant use AE’s) on anyone on the staircase. Again not true. If he is on the bridge and that door is open (which usually it is) he has full use of his breath weapon all the way down the stairs. I’m expecting to be hosting a Nagafen raid very soon if you wish to tag along and check it out I’d be more than happy to show you our tactics and see if the clerics are nailed.<br>
<br>
That being all said I have a few other scenarios to present to you, which relate more closely to the Conquest Guild.<br>
<br>
Most of the points of contention dealt with the exploitation of specific things within the game. Those being (I believe) pathing, and improper use of buffs to negate effects. Here are a few examples I can remember since I was about lvl 5 hunting in CB that I know are used on a day to day basis. Some of these I admit have been used by me, others are too far beyond me to accomplish right now and I only know of by hearing others talk about it.<br>
<br>
In CrushBone : There is a dead spot where nothing can attack or even register your existence. Upon entering you go left across the bridge and back to the right. Instead of going left again to go up the mini ramp down to the Slaver mines, go straight instead. There is a little ledge there right over the water were nothing can attack you, even if you already have agro. Problem? Pathing.<br>
<br>
In CrushBone : A common method for casters to kill Dvinn is – pull him to the front near the jump to trainer hill. Jump onto the ledge, blast, when he gets to you, jump down, blast. And so on until he’s either dead or you run out of Stamina. Problem? Pathing.<br>
<br>
In Kurn’s Tower : Right inside the entrance there is a horrible pathing error. If you stand on one set of tiles the creature comes to you, if you need to heal or anything, simply step one set of tiles to either side. The mob will walk out, around the pillars, along the outside wall and then back down the row of tiles to you. Same by stepping back to the original tiles. Problem? Pathing.<br>
<br>
In The Overthere : Everyone knows about the Fear wall. One of my guildmates (a druid) who was way too low lvl for the zone and was passing through, was attacked by a cactus, feared it (unknowingly right into the wall) and headed into SkyFire to clear agro. He was suspended for trying to run from a mob and had no clue what the wall did. I believe so far it is one of the only publicly known suspension points. So if it’s a simple pathing problem why not change the pathing there? Problem? Pathing.<br>
<br>
In Karnors : A very common tactic with Venril Sathir (from what I hear) is to have one tank pretty much solo him with a couple enches chain casting Rune onto him. Since Rune has no technical life of its own, VS has nothing to drain and therefore can’t heal himself. Is this considered a buff exploit? If so then it should be no problem to convert it so that Rune actually does give life. Problem? Buff Missuse.<br>
<br>
In Cobolt Scar: I’ve often heard from a very good friend about their tactic with Lodizal (the big turtle). They say he can easily be killed with 1 group of lvl 58 – 60’s. How you ask? Easy, since he and the otters are natural enemies, train him onto them, he will eventually kill them all but with about 10% life left, at that point he’s easy pickings. Solution? Make it so he and the otters aren’t natural enemies. Problem? Game Exploitation.<br>
<br>
And lastly I have to ask about this one.<br>
<br>
&quot;8.5.4.2 The key to determining whether a person is exploiting is not in the activity, but is the intent. A player that is using a rain spell to kill masses of monsters may not know it's an exploit, but instead believe that this is simply the function of the spell. It is the responsibility of the Guide to educate the player and ensure that the intention to exploit is present.&quot;<br>
<br>
That can’t be serious. If an AE spell was NOT designed to hit multiple targets then why was it created so it could? If this is an exploit then you need to go around and find every Druid that ever multi kited and ban them too. I don’t use any of my AE spells ever since they’re a waste of time in my eyes as a mage and so I don’t bother but to other classes it’s a much used tool. Besides, if it was not designed around hitting multiple targets why is there more than one chain of AE’s? There’s the rain spells (hitting multiple mobs multiple times with 1 cast) as well as the AE DD’s. To claim that this is not the purpose of the spell is contradictory to its creation and frankly is laughable. Without changing the spell, no one is going to stop using it on multiple mobs.<br>
